<subSubSection id="C368652E935C8E01F2FAFCF5FE01FBB6" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935C8E01F2FAFCF5FE0FFBDA" blockId="5.[151,1437,763,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">
In the same box of Chaudoir's collection containing the beetles of Dejean (box number 175) it is also found the 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935C8E01F2FCFC19FF20FC6E" box="[193,241,907,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F325FC19FCCDFC6E" authority="Dejean, 1829: 275" authorityName="Dejean" authorityPageNumber="275" authorityYear="1829" box="[280,796,906,933]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="oblitus" subSpecies="patruelis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F325FC19FD93FC6E" box="[280,578,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">Harpalus oblitus patruelis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F077FC19FCCDFC6E" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[586,796,906,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829: 275</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, together with other specimens, bearing various kinds of labels: white card with glued beetle/white card with glued genitalia/white card “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F620FC3DFB50FC02" box="[1053,1153,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patruelis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F620FC3DFB50FC02" box="[1053,1153,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">patruelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Hispania”/red card “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935C8E01F29CFC41FF3BFC26" box="[161,234,979,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">TYPE</typeStatus>
”/white card “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F3BAFC41FD95FC26" authority="Dej." authorityName="Dej." box="[391,580,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patruelis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F3BAFC41FDDCFC26" box="[391,525,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. patruelis</emphasis>
Dej.
</taxonomicName>
= subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F0C2FC41FC2BFC26" authority="Dej. Z. Mylnar" box="[767,1018,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">oblitus Dej. Z. Mylnář</taxonomicName>
det. 1973”/ Kataev/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F6D9FC41FA4DFC26" box="[1252,1436,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">Harpalus oblitus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F2AAFC65FEBFFBDA" authority="B. Kataev" authorityName="B. Kataev" box="[151,366,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patruelis">patruelis B. Kataev</taxonomicName>
det 2002.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935C8E01F2FAFB89FE01FBB6" blockId="5.[151,1437,763,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">
The taxonomy and distribution of the subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F12EFB89FC53FBFE" box="[787,898,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F12EFB89FC53FBFE" box="[787,898,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. oblitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F672FB89FB24FBFE" author="Kataev, B. M." box="[1103,1269,1051,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" pagination="65 - 95" refId="ref11316" refString="Kataev, B. M. (1993) Zhuzhelitsy gruppy oblitus roda Harpalus Latr. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 72, 65 - 95. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1993">Kataev (1993)</bibRefCitation>
. There are two currently recognized subspecies: the nominal one occupies the eastern Mediterranean whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F6FFFBADFA4CFB92" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[1218,1437,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="oblitus" subSpecies="patruelis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F6FFFBADFA4CFB92" box="[1218,1437,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. oblitus patruelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in the western part.
</paragraph>
